Step 1:
Download MSI installation file from:
https://jenkins.io/download/
Follow instructins to complete installation.
or Download the latest version of jenkins.war file from:
https://updates.jenkins-ci.org/download/war (this is the official website of Jenkins).

Step 2:
Create a folder with name 'Jenkins' in your C: directory and move the downloaded jenkins.war in it.
Type cmd in windows "Run" to open command prompt and navigate to C:\Jenkins
Execute 'java -jar Jenkins.war' command and it will start installing Jenkins.
Follow instructins to complete installation.

Step 3:
Configure Jenkins to run @tests testng by maven following below youtube guide:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eIldJE4tSlA

Step 4:
Configure Jenkins to scheduling a Build following below youtube guide:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xRhEkLxmi0s
More examples:
http://www.bogotobogo.com/DevOps/Jenkins/Jenkins_Scheduling_Job.php
http://blogs.microsoft.co.il/meravk/2015/06/10/how-to-schedule-a-build-in-jenkins
https://itisatechiesworld.wordpress.com/jenkins-related-articles/jenkins-configuration/jenkins-scheduling-jenkins-jobs-for-a-specific-time

Step 5:
Configure Jenkins to send Email on build failure to gmail following below youtube guide:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9JZS98NfpWk
